2. Let $P(x_0,y_0)(y_0≠0,y_0≠±1)$, $Q(2y_Q-2,y_Q)$, $S(x_S,0)$. Since points C, P, Q are collinear, $\overrightarrow{CP}//\overrightarrow{CQ}$, that is, $(x_0-2)y_Q=y_0(2y_Q-4)$, solve to get $y_Q= rac{4y_0}{2y_0-x_0+2}$, and then obtain the coordinates of Q as $\left( rac{4y_0+2x_0-4}{2y_0-x_0+2}, rac{4y_0}{2y_0-x_0+2}ight)$;
